From 92dbcf2b43f495db0833cfcaae1ee1485b175214 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ramya Gnanasekar <quic_rgnanase@quicinc.com>
Date: Fri, 20 Dec 2024 23:54:49 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:CP:wifi:ath12k: Fix phymode bandwidth update
 sequence

During channel switch, when bandwidth is upgraded phymode update should
happen first followed by channel width update and viceversa during
bandwidth downgrade.

The sequence is decided by comparing current bandwidth and previous
bandwidth updated during peer association. For station mode the
bandwidth is never updated causing it to be default 0. When comparision
happens during bandwidth downgrade, the current bandwidth is always greater
than previous bandwidth causing phymode to update first which results in
Q6 crash due to wrong
sequence.

Fix by updating the bandwidth during association for station mode as
well.

Patch-work: None
Patch-dependency: None

Signed-off-by: Ramya Gnanasekar <quic_rgnanase@quicinc.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
@@ -3925,6 +3925,10 @@ static void ath12k_bss_assoc(struct ath1
 		return;
 	}
 
+        spin_lock_bh(&ar->data_lock);
+        arsta->bw = ath12k_mac_ieee80211_sta_bw_to_wmi(ar, link_sta);
+        spin_unlock_bh(&ar->data_lock);
+
 	rcu_read_unlock();
 
 	/* keep this before ath12k_wmi_send_peer_assoc_cmd() */
